{"name":"Geiger Counter","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Geiger%20Counter.webp","data":{"description":"<p>A Geiger counter is a relatively simple tool, used to detect ionizing radiation. This is displayed on a small gauge, and signaled by a characteristic ticking sound, a common feature of counters, generated by the electronics for easy detection and monitoring of radiation.</p>","favorite":false,"weight":"8","cost":"325","quantity":1,"rarity":3,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Allows a </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>PER + Survival</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">test, difficulty 1, to determine if there is radiation present in an area, and how much.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"04EUZHKRZkOLI6R3"}
{"name":"Signal Flare","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Signal%20Flare.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A small pyrotechnic device which burns brightly, generating a bright light for a short while. They&rsquo;re also extremely hot and can be used to ignite flammable substances and materials if placed close enough.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">These are larger and bulkier than the flares fired from a flare gun.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"0.5","cost":"10","quantity":1,"rarity":1,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Generates bright light within close range until the end of the current scene, One use only.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"0Oef3hKArDH0ozme"}
{"name":"Holotags","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Holotags.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A small, durable, identifying item used by the Brotherhood of Steel. Holotags contain information to identify their wearer in case of death. They also act as a &ldquo;black box&rdquo; data recorder for a suit of Power Armor, providing the Brotherhood record of the deeds of their fallen warriors. Though not especially valuable by themselves, the Brotherhood often pays a reward to any who bring in holotags they find.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"0.2","cost":"5","quantity":1,"rarity":2,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Identifies the fallen</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"1RwlzEf4sKDeqt6T"}
{"_id":"2Mk6xnaG4lUYcyPZ","name":"Pip-Boy","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Pip-Boy.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A Personal Information Processor manufactured by RobCo Industries. Under partnership with Vault-Tec, they were issued to many vault residents, though due to production constraints and ongoing development, different vaults received shipments of different versions of the Pip-Boy. The versions most encountered are variants of the Pip-Boy 2000 and Pip-Boy 3000, which are designed to be secured upon the wearer&rsquo;s wrist. Many models were designed with biometric locks, preventing them from being removed while the wearer still lives.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A Pip-Boy is powered by an internal fission battery, providing a working lifespan for the device far greater than the expected life of its wearer (and, indeed, many Pip-Boys have been handed down within communities or families as heirlooms), and the device itself is sturdy enough to withstand basically anything.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Not all Pip-Boys contain the same functions, but the common functions are:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A personal status indicator allows the wearer to see a report on their current health and wellbeing and any medical problems currently afflicting them.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The device maintains an ongoing log of the wearer&rsquo;sactivities, journey, and condition, and place for&nbsp; personal recordings to be made in either text or audio forms.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">An inbuilt holotape reader allows the device to accept compact holotapes, able to read and playback audio, video, data, and even games.</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It also functions as a compass, a radio, and a Geiger counter, and can generate light from its screen equivalent to a flashlight.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In addition, all Pip-Boy units aid their wearer during combat thanks to the </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">V</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">ault Tec </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">A</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">ssisted </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">T</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">argeting </span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">S</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">ystem, or V.A.T.S. A character equipped with a Pip-Boy may use V.A.T.S. when they make an attack, ignoring the normal difficulty increase for targeting a specific location on the enemy.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"0","cost":"0","quantity":1,"rarity":0,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">See description</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}}}
{"_id":"4yPdCW6eqKxwsouC","name":"Vault-Tec Canteen","type":"consumable","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Vault%20Canteen.webp","data":{"description":"<p>A Vault-Tec Canteen containing purified water.</p>","favorite":false,"weight":"1","cost":"2","quantity":1,"rarity":0,"stashed":false,"consumableType":"beverage","hp":3,"effect":"","irradiated":false,"alcoholic":false,"duration":"","addictive":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.eGYdNvgD4niJ7wPf"}}}
{"name":"Pack Brahmin","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Pack%20Brahmin.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A large, two-headed mutant female cow used as a pack animal. They can carry up to 500 lbs. of weight.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The brahmin can also be milked once a day, requiring an </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>AGI + Survival</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">test with a difficulty of 1. Success means the brahmin produces one brahmin milk, plus one extra for each AP spent (maximum 5 brahmin milk). A brahmin also produces 2</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">CD</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"color: #1d4596;\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">units of fertilizer each day.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /><br /></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"-","cost":"200","quantity":1,"rarity":3,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A mutant cow that carries heavy loads and produces milk and fertilizer.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"AxlvfYmnlHm4lv3H"}
{"name":"Trinket","type":"miscellany","img":"icons/commodities/treasure/broach-jewel-gold-blue.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A personal trinket that hold aparticular sentimental value for your character.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"0","cost":"0","quantity":1,"rarity":0,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Once per quest, outside of combat, you can have your character spend a few moments looking at the trinket, thinking about what it means to them. If you do, you regain 1 Luck Point.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VtmvHqkkEMv5VciA"}},"_id":"B6NLVWYoeyTHjkSy"}
{"_id":"C8VnrdZyzEmFMn12","name":"Backpack, Large","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Backpack%2C%20Large.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Available in a few different sizes, backpacks are invaluable for carrying larger quantities of items around. Most characters are assumed to be carrying items in pockets, belt pouches, and assorted bags and sacks, but a proper backpack helps carry items more easily and more efficiently. At least, if you don&rsquo;t have a pack brahmin or something else to carry your burdens.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"1","cost":"60","quantity":1,"rarity":2,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Wearer adds +10xSTR to maximum Carry weight</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}}}
{"name":"First Aid Kit","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/First%20Aid%20Kit.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A pack full of bandages, antiseptic spray, and other tools useful in helping clean and bind injuries in the field. First aid kits also often come with Stimpaks and RadAway, but these are used and tracked separately.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"4","cost":"200","quantity":1,"rarity":2,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Heal +2 HP upon succeeding at the First Aid action.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"CbRCVS1lRefztbjg"}
{"_id":"Eo4wYNKkgy1QEuHu","name":"Flashlight","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Flashlight.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A sturdy, battery-operated light source that can easily be directed to points of interest. Long-lasting, high-capacity batteries keep the light working for a long time.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /><br /></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"2","cost":"100","quantity":1,"rarity":3,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Generates bright light in a single zone within Medium range; the user may choose which zone is illuminated.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}}}
{"name":"Holotape Player","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Holotape%20Player.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A small device for playing back audio recorded to holotape, producing the sound out of a small speaker or into a connected set of headphones (not included). Video and data holotapes cannot be played back on this device, as it lacks a screen to display them&mdash;such tapes need to be played from a desk terminal or similar computer.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"3","cost":"250","quantity":1,"rarity":2,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Allows playback of audio holotapes.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"JSA4C72S0DKXKXCA"}
{"_id":"Mu1DfOJGmNnTpTwv","name":"Scrap","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Scrap.webp","data":{"description":"<p>Metal Scraps.</p>","favorite":false,"weight":"1","cost":"0","quantity":1,"rarity":0,"stashed":false,"effect":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Yuz3VJlUWGFrmkix"}}}
{"name":"Multi-Tool","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Multi-Tool.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A handy little device, containing a set of pliers, some wire cutters, a variety of small wrenches and screw drivers, and other small tools, all built into a single tool. Different parts fold out of the handles as needed. Ideal for someone who needs basic tools but is still travelling light.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"1","cost":"100","quantity":1,"rarity":2,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Reduce the difficulty of </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Repair </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">tests by 1 (minimum 0)</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"ORE9P7hoNmYp0uV3"}
{"name":"Radio","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Radio.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A device which receives radio signals and translates them back into intelligible sounds. Used both before and after the War for entertainment purposes and emergency messaging alike, a radio is still only as good as the signal it receives. Most regions of the wastelands have a few radio stations active, playing old music for anyone with a working receiver, and a variety of groups make use of the remaining radio towers to broadcast signals to their members over long distances, but the range of these signals is still fairly limited.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"2","cost":"75","quantity":1,"rarity":2,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Picks up and plays radio transmissions.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"Q8OdMRYPxXXYtItd"}
{"name":"Junk","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Junk.webp","data":{"description":"","favorite":false,"weight":"2","cost":"2","quantity":1,"rarity":0,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p>S<span class=\"fontstyle0\">alvaging items takes 10 minutes per item being salvaged and requires an </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">INT + Repair </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">test with a difficulty of 0. Roll 1</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">C</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"color: #1d4596;\">D </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">for each junk item salvaged: you receive </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">common materials </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">equal to the total rolled. You may roll +1</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\">C</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"color: #1d4596;\">D </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">for every AP spent after succeeding on this test, as you salvage more efficiently and secure more materials.</span> </p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">If you have the Scrapper perk, you also receive one </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">uncommon material </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">for each effect rolled. If you have two ranks in the Scrapper perk, you&rsquo;ll also receive one </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">rare material </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">for every two Effects rolled.<br /></span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Consumable items cannot be salvaged: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">you cannot unmix chems, nor uncook meat.</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\"></span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\">You cannot salvage ammunition: </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">the means to do so requires tools that are nearly impossible to find in the wasteland.<br /></span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Common materials</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">include wood, steel, plastic, rubber, cloth, concrete, bone, and ceramics; substances that are easy to find and easy to salvage. A single unit of common materials has a cost of 1 cap, and a weight of 1.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Uncommon materials</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">are rarer and harder to salvage, and include copper, aluminum, lead, silver, as well as cork, glass, fertilizer, fiberglass, and small components such as gears, springs, and screws. A single unit of uncommon materials has a cost of 3 caps, and a weight of 1.</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Rare materials</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">are the rarest and most difficult to salvage. Asbestos, ballistic fiber, circuitry, fiber optics, corrosive and antiseptic chemicals, and even nuclear material are found in many items, but are difficult to salvage. A single unit of rare materials has a cost of 5 caps and a weight of 1.</span></span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NQNOCKb5zMwYZkhv"}},"_id":"QSex6qCu63bhIzz9"}
{"name":"Deluxe Toolkit","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Deluxe%20Toolkit.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A heavy, but still technically portable, handled metal box containing an assortment of tools of different shapes, sizes, and functions, for opening and repairing a variety of mechanical and electronic devices. Having the right tool at your disposal can make most routine repairs simpler and can even allow you to attempt more ambitious projects away from the comforts of home.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"20","cost":"150","quantity":1,"rarity":3,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Reduce the difficulty of </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Repair </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">tests by 1 (minimum 0), May attempt Repair tests which normally require a workbench or similar at +1 difficulty</span> <br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /><br /></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"W3eOSjZTx2kQKTAx"}
{"_id":"Za7QuBd9s2W0E7bv","name":"Backpack, Small","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Backpack%2C%20Small.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Available in a few different sizes, backpacks are invaluable for carrying larger quantities of items around. Most characters are assumed to be carrying items in pockets, belt pouches, and assorted bags and sacks, but a proper backpack helps carry items more easily and more efficiently. At least, if you don&rsquo;t have a pack brahmin or something else to carry your burdens.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"1","cost":"30","quantity":1,"rarity":1,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Wearer adds +5xSTR to maximum Carry weight</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}}}
{"_id":"aLW64Cys5HmUqs5T","name":"Lock Pick Set","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Lockpick%20set.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A rolled-up leather case containing an assortment of picks and tension wrenches for opening mechanical locks, as an alternative to the cruder &ldquo;screwdriver and bobby pins&rdquo; method. Sturdier than the improvised method, but a set can become useless if too many of the picks or wrenches break.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"2","cost":"150","quantity":1,"rarity":2,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Reduces difficulty of </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Lockpick </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">tests by 1 (minimum 0), After 3 complications, the set is broken.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}}}
{"name":"Torch","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Torch.webp","data":{"description":"<p>A long branch or length of scrap metal, with a head wrapped in cloth soaked in a flammable liquid such as alcohol or gasoline. A decent enough improvised light source, and reusable to an extent.</p>","favorite":false,"weight":"1","cost":"10","quantity":1,"rarity":1,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Generates bright light within close range until the end of the current scene, Requires an </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>INT + Survival</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">test to light, difficulty 1, +1 for each previous use.</span><br style=\"font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\" /><br /></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"kITvQyuobJRkO9xz"}
{"_id":"kMm2sFrvlvSO3H4K","name":"Bobby Pin","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Bobby%20Pin.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A flexible double-pronged hairpin, made of metal or plastic, they were used before the Great War to hold hair in place. They&rsquo;re also useful for picking locks if you know how.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"0","cost":"1","quantity":1,"rarity":0,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Reduces difficulty of </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Lockpick </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">tests by 1 (minimum 1), One bobby pin breaks per complication rolled.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}}}
{"name":"Doctor's Bag","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Doctors%20Bag.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A well-stocked bag of medical supplies and useful tools for the science of healing. A bit cumbersome to haul around, but the people whose lives you save will thank you for the effort.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A doctor&rsquo;s bag may also contain one-use medical supplies like Stimpaks, purified water, and RadAway. These are tracked and used separately.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"10","cost":"300","quantity":1,"rarity":3,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Reduce the difficulty of </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>Medicine</strong> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">tests by 1 (minimum 0), When providing long-term care, allows care of up to 2 additional patients</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"ohAm7AnZFYKEWVNb"}
{"name":"Holodisk","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Holodisks.webp","data":{"description":"<p>A holotape (alternatively called a holodisk, holo-disc, or a THT (Tape Holography Technology) tape) is a durable laser-readable storage device produced by Wattz Electronics, based on the tape holography technology, storing their information safely for extended periods of time.</p>","favorite":false,"weight":"0","cost":"0","quantity":1,"rarity":1,"stashed":false,"effect":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.g11I1PI9m65qBVEc"}},"_id":"slSTqCeqJdWysgu3"}
{"name":"Electronic Lockpicker","type":"miscellany","img":"../artwork/Tools%20and%20Utility%20Items/Electronic%20Lockpicker.webp","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Difficult to find in the wasteland, the </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><em>Wattz Electronics Micromanipulator</em> </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">electronic lockpick is a potent tool that can pick mechanical and electronic locks more efficiently than a person can alone. However, they&rsquo;re delicate, and can break down if misused.</span></p>","favorite":false,"weight":"4","cost":"375","quantity":1,"rarity":4,"stashed":false,"effect":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Reduces difficulty of </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Lockpick </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">tests by 2 (minimum 0), Ignores first complication rolled, Breaks if two or more complications are rolled at once.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"I8FU1gA0rIKN7NHn":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NxOe9fSH0NASqfN3"}},"_id":"xyYWcz4Q0gixhVmE"}
